comments: Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Murphy III (NOP) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off ball.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) places his hand against Williamson's (NOP) side during his drive and marginal body contact occurs.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and marginal contact occurs as Robinson-Earl maintains verticality during the shot.
Alvarado (NOP) brings his hands towards Robinson-Earl's (OKC) side and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Alvarado (NOP) is moving alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and absorbs the marginal contact as Gilgeous-Alexander spins towards the basket.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) loses control of the ball on his own, and upon re-gaining possession he does not take more than two steps after his gather.
Alvarado (NOP) brings his arm down and initiates contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and marginal body contact occurs during Williamson's drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Pokusevski (OKC) and Murphy III (NOP) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Alvarado (NOP) brings his forearm towards Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during Gilgeous-Alexander's drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) leaves his feet to pass and he releases the ball before returning to the floor.
Alvarado (NOP) is already in Dort's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Dort (OKC) is late to the spot and does not establish a legal guarding position in Williamson's (NOP) path prior to contact.
The game is stopped due to a clock malfunction.  After correcting the clock, play correctly resumes with the Thunder retaining possession with 44.4 seconds remaining on the game clock.
Jones (NOP) moves somewhat forward towards Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Gilegous-Alexander (OKC) steps forward into Daniels' (NOP) path and initiates contact that affects Daniels' SQBR.

Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) cleanly ties up Daniels (NOP), and a jump ball is correctly called.  At the time of the whistle, Daniels did not have full control of the ball as Alvarado (NOP) attempts to call a timeout.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
The timeout called by the Pelicans is recognized and awarded prior to a potential eight second violation.
Dort (OKC) briefly places his hand to Alvardo's (NOP) front and immediately removes his had while defending the drive.
Dort (OKC) moves forward into Daniels' (NOP) body and delivers contact that dislodges him from his rebounding position.
Jones (NOP) moves laterally into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path, and does not establish a legal guarding position in his path prior to contact.
Pokusevski (OKC) commits a take foul on Jones (NOP).
